property.name: syncWord
property.label: Synchronization word
property.desc: 32-bit synchronization word that the receiver uses to detect the start of the packet

property.name: whitening
property.label: Whitening
property.desc: Whitening is applied to the packet data before transmission, to make the transmitted bit stream "random" and DC-free

property.name: packetLengthSize
property.label: Payload length
property.desc:
Fixed: Length is not indicated in the packet, the fixed packet length is given by CMD_GENERIC_RX.maxPktLen for packet RX.

Variable (default): 8-bit length field at the start of the packet indicates the payload size (including the RF test's 16-bit sequence number, if used).

property.name: txMinPacketInterval
property.label: Minimum packet interval
property.desc: Minimum packet transmission interval, in milliseconds (0 = transmit as fast as possible)

property.name: rxFixedPayloadLength
property.label: Fixed payload length
property.desc: The packet payload size (including 16-bit sequence number, if used)

data.name: LRF_PBE_CFG_MSK_RAM
data.desc: PBE ram register config for generic operation
